Bunopithecus hoolock.EditorialNote: This class is not intended to present a normative,          comprehensive, taxonomic hierarchy, but rather is provided as an approximate indication of          the phylogenetic relatedness amongst the taxonomic groups nested under it (BB)., Note GBIF considers this an unconfirmed name and doesn't classify it beyond Class Mammalia.  For this reason, the species Bunopithecus and Hylobates have not been declared disjoint.
